You can view the Full computer name on the System Properties Control Panel applet’s Computer Name page.

The DNS suffix of a computer is the part of the computer’s DNS name that follows the host name element. If you have a computer named mypc.accounting.contoso.com, the host name is mypc and the DNS suffix is accounting.contoso.com.

default suffix is .local

you can also omit the suffix sometimes

DNS can recongize the device and add the suffix automatically

(useful for example in Remote Desktop )

TO CHANGE DNS SUFFIX


on start type
Advanced system settings

Click on tab 'Computer Name'
Click on change
Click on more
and type a suffix in 'primary dns suffix'

leave checked 'Change primary dns suffix when domain membership changes'

remember! hostnames are NOT case sensitive
